headline: Digital Realty Trust Targets AI Demand With Malaysia Entry And Supply Deal
summary: Digital Realty Trust (NYSE:DLR) has entered Malaysia with the acquisition of the TelcoHub 1 data center. The company also signed a supply agreement with Schneider Electric to support AI focused data center infrastructure. These moves extend Digital Realty Trust's footprint in Southeast Asia while targeting growing AI infrastructure demand. Digital Realty Trust, trading at $167.44, is adding Malaysia to its global data center footprint at a time when its longer term returns have been mixed,...
